    {
      "id": "a2fda150243c1007534fa78d70c0a617d5dc82ca",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-10 02:14:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "75ca2bf0c79eb197ec7419c0653f94bb77890af5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-25 23:25:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(13 comments)\n\nDid you actually see problems with the LDLM code, or is that only a result of the current defaults being a function of the RAM size?  It doesn't seem likely that there are any problems in this area, and given that an ldlm_lock + ldlm_resource are 906 bytes each it means with 2B locks this is consuming close to 2TB of RAM just for the lock structures even without any of the data.  Most of the LDLM API changes are only for lock cancellation, which can't grow so large, so it would probably be better to remove this part of the changes from the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "675972593f409703d6c1eb0fc7bac52d12ce013b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-26 06:17:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThis is very similar to http://review.whamcloud.com/10486 but not quite identical.\n\nI'm OK with this patch using \"long\" instead of \"__u64\" everywhere, but the patch isn't quite identical in both cases.  It is probably worthwhile to compare all of the changes in http://review.whamcloud.com/10486 to see if they are no longer needed because of other code changes, or if they were missed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "771b97197a12b0d13eb35fb45fbb76f18978c2fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-30 04:12:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review\n\nWhen I reviewed this patch, I compared it with http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10486/. I think most of the changes there is included in this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
